1 Section 1. Section 79-2,144, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska,
2 is amended to read:
3 79-2,144 (1) The state school security director appointed pursuant
4 to section 79-2,143 shall be responsible for providing leadership and
5 support for safety and security for the public schools. Duties of the
6 director include, but are not limited to:
7 (a) (1) Collecting safety and security plans, required pursuant to
8 rules and regulations of the State Department of Education relating to
9 accreditation of schools, and other school security information from each
10 school system in Nebraska. School districts shall provide the state
11 school security director with the safety and security plans of the school
12 district, annual inspection information of protective door assemblies,
13 door-locking systems, and double-entry doors of school buildings within
14 the school district, and any other security information requested by the
15 director, but any plans or information submitted by a school district may
16 be withheld by the department pursuant to subdivision (9) of section
17 84-712.05;
18 (b) (2) Recommending minimum standards for school security on or
19 before January 1, 2016, to the State Board of Education;
20 (c) (3) Conducting an assessment of the security of each public
21 school building, which assessment shall be completed by August 31, 2019;
22 (d) Establishing standards related to protective door assemblies in
23 each school building that is used for the instruction of students, which
24 shall include requiring that every school board cause an annual
25 inspection of all applicable protective door assemblies to be conducted
26 by a trained inspector with appropriate knowledge, training, and
27 experience relating to door assemblies and building security;
28 (e) (4) Identifying deficiencies in school security based on the
29 minimum standards adopted by the State Board of Education and making
30 recommendations to school boards for remedying such deficiencies;
31 (f) (5) Establishing security awareness and preparedness tools and
-2-

