1 training programs for public school staff;
2 (g) (6) Establishing research-based model instructional programs for
3 staff, students, and parents to address the underlying causes for violent
4 attacks on schools;
5 (h) (7) Overseeing behavioral and mental health training, with a
6 focus on suicide awareness and prevention in public schools pursuant to
7 section 79-2,146;
8 (i) (8) Establishing tornado preparedness standards which shall
9 include, but not be limited to, ensuring that every school conducts at
10 least two tornado drills per year;
11 (j) (9) Responding to inquiries and requests for assistance relating
12 to school security from private, denominational, and parochial schools;
13 (k) (10) Recommending curricular and extracurricular materials to
14 assist school districts in preventing and responding to cyberbullying and
15 digital citizenship issues; and
16 (l) (11) Carrying out the department's responsibilities under the
17 School Safety and Security Reporting System Act.
18 (2) For purposes of this section, protective door assemblies means
19 (a) doors with panic hardware or fire exit hardware, (b) door assemblies
20 in exit enclosures, (c) electronically controlled egress doors, and (d)
21 door assemblies with special locking arrangements, such as delayed
22 egress, sensor-released egress doors, and elevator-lobby doors.
23 Sec. 2. Original section 79-2,144, Reissue Revised Statutes of
24 Nebraska, is repealed.
